sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino<br/>5001/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant BBR as payload-processing (BBR)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Limitador as Kuadrant Limitador<br/>8081/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant KServe as KServe Model Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS
    participant ExtProvider as External Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,KServe: Flow 1: Internal Model Inference (LLMInferenceService)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-* or OpenShift token
        Gateway->>Authorino: Evaluate AuthPolicy<br/>gRPC mTLS (Istio)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTP (NetworkPolicy-restricted)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: {valid, username, groups}
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTP (NetworkPolicy-restricted)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: {subscription, token limits}
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Allow + inject X-MaaS-Username,<br/>X-MaaS-Group, X-MaaS-Subscription headers
        Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc: extract model from body<br/>gRPC/TLS (DestinationRule SIMPLE)
        BBR-->>Gateway: X-Gateway-Model-Name header
        Gateway->>Limitador: Evaluate TokenRateLimitPolicy<br/>gRPC mTLS (Istio)
        Limitador-->>Gateway: Allow/Deny (token quota check)
        Gateway->>KServe: Forward to model pod via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/8000 (Authorization header stripped)
        KServe-->>Client: Inference Response (JSON/SSE)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 2: External Model Inference (ExternalModel)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token
        Gateway->>Authorino: Evaluate AuthPolicy<br/>gRPC mTLS
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Allow + identity headers
        Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc: model extraction +<br/>provider resolution + API translation +<br/>credential injection from Secret
        BBR-->>Gateway: Transformed request +<br/>X-Gateway-Model-Name + provider API key
        Gateway->>Limitador: TokenRateLimitPolicy check<br/>gRPC mTLS
        Limitador-->>Gateway: Allow/Deny
        Gateway->>ExtProvider: Forward via ServiceEntry +<br/>DestinationRule TLS origination<br/>HTTPS/443 + injected API key
        ExtProvider-->>Client: Provider Response (translated back)
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: API Key Creation
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer (OpenShift token or existing key)
        Gateway->>Authorino: Evaluate maas-api AuthPolicy
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Allow + X-MaaS-Username header
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTP/8080
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT key hash (SHA-256,<br/>key_id salt, show-once)<br/>TCP/5432
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Stored
        MaaSAPI-->>Client: {api_key: "sk-oai-{id}_{secret}"}<br/>Plaintext shown once only
    end

    rect rgb(245, 230, 255)
        Note over Client,KServe: Flow 4: Model Discovery (/v1/models)
        Client->>Gateway: GET /v1/models<br/>Auth: Bearer token
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTP/8080
        Note over MaaSAPI: Filter MaaSModelRef list<br/>from informer cache by<br/>user subscriptions
        MaaSAPI->>KServe: Probe /v1/models per model<br/>HTTPS/8000 (InsecureSkipVerify)<br/>Authorization + X-Maas-Subscription passthrough
        KServe-->>MaaSAPI: Model availability status
        MaaSAPI-->>Client: OpenAI-compatible model list<br/>Cache-Control: no-store
    end
